kuznet@ms2.inr.ac.ru wrote:
> If you want to get something really useful from multiple links,
> do not attach them to single broadcast wire and use router instead.
> 
> If you do not believe, write 1 to /proc/sys/net/ipv4/conf/*/hidden
> and check.
To be honest I only want to do this to stress test my 8139too driver on
SMP...  I am not implementing this in production.  But thanks for
clearing up a misconception -- that multiple NICs on the same wire is
really not useful.
thanks much for the info.
